Send a written reminder within 10 days before the expiration of the prescribed period to accountable offices concerned; and

If the accountable officer fail to liquidate his/her cash advance within the prescribed period, delete the name of the official or employee concerned from the subsequent payrolls until such time that his/her cash advance has been fully liquidated;

In the case of the deceased or those who have been separated from service, the City shall make representations with the proper prosecuting agencies of the government towards the institution of the necessary proceedings for the recovery of the amount of the cash advance as provided in Section 4.1 of COA Circular No. 86-256; and

Prepare request for authority to write-off dormant unliquidated cash advances from the books of the agency as provided under COA Circular No. 2016-005 [re: Guidelines and Procedures on the Write-off of Dormant Receivable Accounts, Unliquidated Cash Advances, and Fund Transfers of National Government Agencies (NGAs), Local Government Units (LGUs) and Government-Owned and Controlled Corporations (GOCCs)].

The Local Chief Executive instruct the City Assessor to provide this Office a photocopy of land titles for parcels of land to ascertain the legality of LGUs ownership; 

Exhaust all possible means to document the legality of ownership of the parcel of lands recorded in the books of accounts through a Transfer Certificate of Title (TCT) or its equivalent in the name of the City Government of Ozamiz pursuant to the existing rules and regulations provided under PD 1445 and GAAM; and

Accounting records on Land Account should reconcile with the Inventory Report of Land by GSO.

Require the accountant to evaluate and identify what and who causes the delay in the submission of the disbursement vouchers and install corrective measures to facilitate and update submission of accounts;

Enjoin the accountant to immediately submit the disbursement vouchers previously mentioned as not submitted as of December 31, 2020; and

Enforce paragraph 2 Section 122 of PD 1445 which provides the automatic suspension of payment of salaries of those officials who fail to submit these documents and reports should there be further delay in the submission of accounts.

